Simple Breakdown of the Paper
This paper explores a method called Entanglement Bootstrap applied to Conformal Field Theories (CFTs) in any number of dimensions.
Core Idea:
Instead of starting with the full Lagrangian or equations of a quantum field theory, the authors try to reconstruct the theory using only local entanglement information (how quantum subsystems are correlated/entangled with each other). 
This is part of a broader research direction that treats quantum entanglement and information as more fundamental than the fields or particles themselves. The goal is to “bootstrap” (build up) the entire theory from entanglement data alone.
This approach is heavily influenced by ideas from quantum information theory, holography (AdS/CFT), and the ER=EPR conjecture.
